{"lemma":"مُغْلَق","slug":"مُغْلَق","root":"غ.ل.ق","root_slug":"غ-ل-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/غ-ل-ق","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n32295","n32296"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D8%BA%D9%92%D9%84%D9%8E%D9%82"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"lock, closure"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bolt"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"active participle of أَغْلَقَ (ʔaḡlaqa)","tags":["active","form-of","participle"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"passive participle of أَغْلَقَ (ʔaḡlaqa): closed, shut","tags":["form-of","participle","passive"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"active participle of غَلَّقَ (ḡallaqa)","tags":["active","form-of","participle"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"passive participle of غَلَّقَ (ḡallaqa)","tags":["form-of","participle","passive"],"examples":[{"text":"قَدْ كُنْتُ فَرَّاجَ أَبْوَابٍ مُغَلَّقَةٍ / ذَبَّ الرِّيَادِ إِذَا مَا خُولِسَ النَّظَرُ"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Tool noun from غَلَقَ (ḡalaqa).\n\nDerived from the active participle of أَغْلَقَ (ʔaḡlaqa, “to close, to lock”).\n\nDerived from the passive participle of أَغْلَقَ (ʔaḡlaqa, “to close, to lock”)."},"ipa":["/miɣ.laq/","/muɣ.liq/","/muɣ.laq/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n32295","headword_ar":"مُغْلَقٌ","root":"glq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guluqN","text_ar":"غُلُقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n32296","headword_ar":"مِغْلَقٌ","root":"glq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"galaqN","text_ar":"غَلَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  Also, (S, O, K, TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"migolaAqN","text_ar":"مِغْلَاقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a dial. var. thereof in this sense, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An arrow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any arrow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"used in the game called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almayosir","text_ar":"المَيْسِر"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O, K:) or, (K,) accord. to Lth, (O,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almigolaqu","text_ar":"المِغْلَقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~ahomu Als~AbiEu","text_ar":"السَّهْمُ السّابِعُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY muDaE~afi Almayosiri","text_ar":"فِى مُضَعَّفِ المَيْسِرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the seventh arrow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"belonging to the class, of the arrows of the game of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almysr","text_ar":"الميسر"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to which manifold portions are assigned;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuDaE~afu","text_ar":"المُضَعَّفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as used in relation to the game called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almysr","text_ar":"الميسر"},{"kind":"text","text":"I do not find expl. otherwise than as an appellation of “ the second of the arrows termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Algufol","text_ar":"الغُفْل"},{"kind":"text","text":", to which are assigned no portion; ” (see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DEf","text_ar":"ضعف"},{"kind":"text","text":", and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safiyHN","text_ar":"سَفِيحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";) and this cannot be here meant, as the seventh arrow (which is commonly called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuEal~aY","text_ar":"المُعَلَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":") has seven portions assigned to it: therefore it seems that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muDaE~af","text_ar":"مُضَعَّف"},{"kind":"text","text":"is here used, if not mistakenly, in a sense which, though admissible, is unusual in a case of this kind]: (O, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"magaAliqu","text_ar":"مَغَالِقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O, K: in the CK [erroneously]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"magaAliyqu","text_ar":"مَغَالِيقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmugaAliqu","text_ar":"المُغَالِقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is one of the epithets applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the winning arrows,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and is not one of their [particular] names; (O, K;) they being"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"those that make what is played-for to be a forfeit to the player"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tugoliqu AlxaTara liloqaAmiri","text_ar":"تُغْلِقُ الخَطَرَ لِلْقَامِرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"): so accord. to Az, who says that Lth has made a mistake in his explanation. (O.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","TA"]}]}}